# Testing and Debugging

## Test Environment

All tests use temporary directories for isolation:
```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use tempfile::TempDir;

    fn setup_test_storage() -> (KnowledgeGraph, TempDir) {
        let temp_dir = TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let cache_dir = get_test_cache_dir();
        let kg = KnowledgeGraph::new(temp_dir.path(), Some(&cache_dir)).unwrap();
        (kg, temp_dir)
    }

    fn get_test_cache_dir() -> PathBuf {
        std::env::var("FASTEMBED_CACHE_PATH")
            .map(PathBuf::from)
            .unwrap_or_else(|_| {
                PathBuf::from(env!("CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR"))
                    .join("target")
                    .join("test_model_cache")
            })
    }
}
```

## Running Tests

```bash
source env.sh                              # Required for RocksDB
cargo test                                 # All tests
cargo test storage                         # Module-specific
cargo test -- --nocapture                  # With stdout
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test -- --nocapture   # Debug logging
cargo test test_name -- --exact            # Single test
```

## Mock vs Real Providers

### Mock (fast, deterministic — use for unit tests)
```rust
struct MockEmbeddingProvider { dimensions: usize }

#[async_trait]
impl EmbeddingProvider for MockEmbeddingProvider {
    async fn embed(&self, text: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>> {
        let mut v = vec![0.1; self.dimensions];
        v[0] = text.len() as f32 / 100.0;
        Ok(v)
    }
    async fn embed_batch(&self, texts: Vec<String>) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        texts.iter().map(|t| self.embed(t)).collect() // simplified
    }
    fn dimensions(&self) -> Result<usize> { Ok(self.dimensions) }
    fn max_tokens(&self) -> Result<usize> { Ok(512) }
    fn provider_type(&self) -> EmbeddingProviderType { /* mock */ }
    fn model_info(&self) -> Option<ModelInfo<EmbeddingModel>> { None }
}
```

### Real FastEmbed (integration tests — slower, requires model download)
```rust
fn create_real_embedding_manager() -> Result<EmbeddingManager> {
    let cache_dir = get_test_cache_dir();
    EmbeddingManager::try_new_local_default(Some(cache_dir))
}
```

### Lemonade Server (integration tests — requires running server)
```rust
async fn create_lemonade_manager() -> Result<EmbeddingManager> {
    EmbeddingManager::try_new_lemonade(
        "http://localhost:8000/api/v1",
        "nomic-embed-text"
    ).await
}
```

## Known Bug Testing

When fixing bugs from ARCHITECTURE.md, write regression tests:

```rust
#[test]
fn test_bug6_import_deduplication() {
    let (graph, _temp) = setup_test_storage();
    // Import same data twice
    // Assert object count doesn't double
}

#[test]
fn test_bug2_similarity_bounded() {
    // Ensure similarity is always in [0, 1]
    let similarity = 1.0 / (1.0 + large_distance);
    assert!(similarity >= 0.0 && similarity <= 1.0);
}
```

## Debugging

### Logging levels
```bash
RUST_LOG=trace                          # Everything
RUST_LOG=debug                          # Development
RUST_LOG=info                           # Normal operation
RUST_LOG=u_forge_ai::storage=debug      # Single module
```

### Structured logging in code
```rust
tracing::info!(
    operation = "create_object",
    object_type = %obj_type,
    duration_ms = start.elapsed().as_millis(),
    "Object created"
);
```

### Common issues

| Symptom | Likely Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| RocksDB compile error | Missing gcc-13 | `source env.sh` |
| Dimension mismatch panic | Wrong embedding model | Check provider dimensions match VectorSearchConfig |
| Search returns empty | HNSW not populated | Ensure add_chunk called before search |
| Negative similarity scores | BUG-2 | Fix: `1.0 / (1.0 + distance)` |
| Duplicate objects after import | BUG-6 | Add find_by_name check before insert |
| Edge references unresolved | BUG-7 | Query storage before session map |

## Performance Testing

```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_embedding_throughput() {
    let start = Instant::now();
    let provider = create_real_embedding_manager().unwrap();
    let texts: Vec<String> = (0..100).map(|i| format!("Test text {}", i)).collect();
    let _ = provider.get_provider().embed_batch(texts).await.unwrap();
    println!("100 embeddings in {:?}", start.elapsed());
}
```

